 :tx/rationale "AUDIT CROSS-CUTTING-SYNTHESIS: The central diagnosis — C8 is both the deepest problem and has the clearest solution path. OBSERVATION: Across all 10 audit dimensions, C8 (Substrate Independence) is the unifying thread. The LIVE index bug (F-INV-001) is a correctness defect; the verification gaps (F-SPEC-001) are coverage deficits. But C8 violations are architectural — they determine whether braid achieves its stated identity as 'infrastructure for organizational learning' or remains 'a DDIS tool.' Quantified: ~180 hardcoded attributes in schema.rs, ~14K LOC of DDIS-specific guidance in the kernel, 3 hardcoded ISP layer constants in trilateral.rs, 5 hardcoded innate concepts, ~23 DDIS-specific counters in MaterializedViews. The solution path is architecturally clear: (1) policy.rs already provides the dynamic configuration pattern, (2) Schema::from_datoms() already provides the C3-compliant loading mechanism, (3) the BoundaryCheck trait already provides the extensible fitness pattern. The work is extraction and generalization, not invention. The 92-hour Wave 2 estimate reflects the LOC volume (primarily the 40h guidance extraction), not architectural uncertainty. The project's theoretical foundations (SEED.md, 433 spec elements, 8 reconciliation types) are the deepest and most rigorous of any project I have audited. The gap is between the depth of the formalism and the breadth of its implementation in the kernel code."
